## API Integration

### Coilpack API Routes (Laravel)

```php
// routes/api.php
use App\Http\Controllers\Api\EntryController;
use App\Http\Controllers\Api\PageController;

Route::prefix('v1')->group(function () {
    Route::get('/entries/{channel}', [EntryController::class, 'index']);
    Route::get('/entries/{channel}/{slug}', [EntryController::class, 'show']);
    Route::get('/pages/{slug}', [PageController::class, 'show']);
    Route::get('/navigation/{menu}', [NavigationController::class, 'index']);
});
```

### API Controller Pattern

```php
// app/Http/Controllers/Api/EntryController.php
namespace App\Http\Controllers\Api;

use Illuminate\Http\JsonResponse;

class EntryController extends Controller
{
    public function index(string $channel): JsonResponse
    {
        $entries = ee('Channel')->getEntries([
            'channel' => $channel,
            'limit' => request()->input('limit', 10),
            'offset' => request()->input('offset', 0),
            'orderby' => 'date',
            'sort' => 'desc',
        ]);

        return response()->json([
            'data' => $entries->map(fn($entry) => [
                'id' => $entry->entry_id,
                'title' => $entry->title,
                'slug' => $entry->url_title,
                'date' => $entry->entry_date,
                'content' => $entry->getCustomField('page_content'),
            ]),
            'total' => $entries->total(),
        ]);
    }
}
```

### Next.js API Client

```typescript
// lib/api.ts
const API_BASE = process.env.COILPACK_API_URL!;

export async function fetchEntries(channel: string, options?: {
  limit?: number;
  offset?: number;
}) {
  const params = new URLSearchParams({
    limit: String(options?.limit ?? 10),
    offset: String(options?.offset ?? 0),
  });

  const res = await fetch(`${API_BASE}/v1/entries/${channel}?${params}`, {
    next: { revalidate: 3600 },
  });

  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`API error: ${res.status}`);
  return res.json();
}

export async function fetchEntry(channel: string, slug: string) {
  const res = await fetch(`${API_BASE}/v1/entries/${channel}/${slug}`, {
    next: { revalidate: 3600 },
  });

  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`API error: ${res.status}`);
  return res.json();
}
```

### Using in Server Components

```tsx
// app/blog/page.tsx
import { fetchEntries } from '@/lib/api';

export default async function BlogPage() {
  const { data: posts } = await fetchEntries('blog', { limit: 10 });

  return (
    <main>
      <h1>Blog</h1>
      {posts.map((post) => (
        <article key={post.slug}>
          <Link href={`/blog/${post.slug}`}>
            <h2>{post.title}</h2>
          </Link>
        </article>
      ))}
    </main>
  );
}
```

## Bilingual Considerations

This project may support bilingual content (EN/FR):
- Language detection via Laravel localization on the backend
- Translation files in `lang/en/` and `lang/fr/`
- Frontend i18n via `next-intl` or similar
- API responses include locale-specific content

## Coding Standards

### PHP (Coilpack/Laravel)
- PSR-12 coding standards
- 4-space indentation
- Type hints for parameters and return types
- Use Laravel's API Resource classes for response formatting

### TypeScript (Next.js)
- Use strict mode; no `any` type
- Define interfaces for all API responses
- Prefer Server Components; use `'use client'` only for interactivity

### CSS
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Mobile-first responsive design

## Important Notes

1. **Always use `ddev` prefix** for backend CLI commands
2. **API routes**: Defined in `routes/api.php`, prefixed with `/api/v1/`
3. **Environment variables**: Backend `.env`, frontend `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix for client-side
4. **CORS**: Configure in Laravel `config/cors.php`
5. **Authentication**: Use Laravel Sanctum for API token management
6. **Cache invalidation**: Clear both EE and Laravel caches: `ddev ee cache:clear && ddev artisan optimize:clear`

